# Optional custom domain for GitHub Pages
# 1. Copy this file to `public/CNAME` (no extension) with your domain only, e.g.:
#    docs.example.com
# 2. In GitHub repo Settings → Pages → Custom domain, set the same host
# 3. Add DNS CNAME (or A records for apex) per GitHub docs
# 4. Update siteUrl / og:image / sitemap hostname in .vitepress/config.mts
#
# Leave CNAME out of the repo until DNS is ready — a wrong CNAME breaks github.io.
